        <main class="policy-section">
            <div class="policy-container">
                <h1 class="policy-title">Cookie Policy & GDPR Compliance</h1>

                <p class="policy-intro">
                    Welcome to Axiom Hub's Cookie Policy. We are committed to protecting your privacy and complying
                    with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) of the European Union. This policy explains
                    in detail how we use cookies and process your personal data.
                </p>

                <div class="highlight-box">
                    <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> November 13, 2025</p>
                    <p><strong>Data Controller:</strong> Axiom Hub's</p>
                    <p><strong>Contact:</strong> contact@axiomhub.eu | Discord: https://discord.gg/wx9gV9Z7Yy</p>
                </div>

                <!-- Section 1: What is a Cookie -->
                <h2 class="policy-section-title">1. What is a Cookie?</h2>
                <div class="policy-content">
                    <p>
                        A cookie is a small text file stored on your device (computer, tablet, smartphone) when you
                        visit a website. Cookies allow the website to remember your actions and preferences over a
                        period of time, so you don't have to re-enter them each time you visit or navigate between
                        pages.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Cookies can be "session cookies" (deleted when you close your browser) or "persistent cookies"
                        (remain on your device until expiration or manual deletion).
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Section 2: Complete Cookie List -->
                <h2 class="policy-section-title">2. Complete List of Cookies We Use</h2>
                <div class="policy-content">
                    <p>
                        Axiom Hub's uses both essential and functional cookies to provide and improve our services.
                        Below is the complete list of all cookies set by our website:
                    </p>

                    <table class="policy-table">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Cookie Name</th>
                                <th>Type</th>
                                <th>Duration</th>
                                <th>Purpose</th>
                                <th>Legal Basis</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td><strong>consent</strong></td>
                                <td>Strictly Necessary</td>
                                <td>1 year</td>
                                <td>Records your consent to use cookies (GDPR compliance)</td>
                                <td>Legal obligation (Art. 6(1)(c) GDPR)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><strong>auth-token</strong></td>
                                <td>Authentication</td>
                                <td>30 days</td>
                                <td>Maintains your authenticated session (JWT token)</td>
                                <td>Contract performance (Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><strong>logged</strong></td>
                                <td>Functional</td>
                                <td>30 days</td>
                                <td>Indicates login status for UI rendering</td>
                                <td>Legitimate interest (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><strong>sessionID</strong></td>
                                <td>Analytics</td>
                                <td>Session (browser close)</td>
                                <td>Tracks unique sessions for analytics (server-side, HttpOnly)</td>
                                <td>Consent (Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><strong>sessionID_client</strong></td>
                                <td>Analytics</td>
                                <td>Session (browser close)</td>
                                <td>Client-side session tracking for page duration analytics</td>
                                <td>Consent (Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR)</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">2.1. Strictly Necessary Cookies</h3>

                    <h4>consent (1 year)</h4>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Purpose:</strong> This cookie is absolutely essential for GDPR compliance. It stores
                        your explicit consent to use cookies on our website.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Data Stored:</strong> Boolean value ("true") indicating consent acceptance.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Legal obligation under GDPR Article 7 (Conditions for consent).
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Security:</strong> HttpOnly, Secure (HTTPS), SameSite=Strict/Lax.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">2.2. Authentication Cookies</h3>

                    <h4>auth-token (30 days)</h4>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Purpose:</strong> Maintains your authenticated session. Contains a JSON Web Token (JWT)
                        that proves your identity without requiring repeated logins.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Data Stored:</strong> Encrypted JWT containing user ID, email, and expiration timestamp.
                        No password is stored.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Necessary for contract performance (providing authentication
                        services) under GDPR Article 6(1)(b).
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Security:</strong> HttpOnly (prevents JavaScript access), Secure (HTTPS only),
                        SameSite=Strict (prevents CSRF attacks).
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Expiration:</strong> 30 days from creation, or upon manual logout.
                    </p>

                    <h4>logged (30 days)</h4>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Purpose:</strong> Boolean flag indicating whether user is logged in. Used for UI
                        rendering (showing/hiding login buttons, user menu, etc.).
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Data Stored:</strong> String value "true" or absence of cookie.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Legitimate interest in providing functional user interface under
                        GDPR Article 6(1)(f).
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Security:</strong> HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Strict/Lax.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">2.3. Analytics Cookies</h3>

                    <h4>sessionID (Session)</h4>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Purpose:</strong> Generates a unique identifier for your browsing session. Used to track
                        unique visitors, page views, and user behavior patterns without identifying you personally.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Data Stored:</strong> UUID v4 (Universally Unique Identifier) - e.g.,
                        "a3d5f8e2-4b1c-4d7e-9f2a-1c8b5e3d4f6a".
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Data Collected:</strong>
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Pages visited (URL paths)</li>
                        <li>Visit timestamps</li>
                        <li>Page duration (time spent on page)</li>
                        <li>Browser name and version (User-Agent parsing)</li>
                        <li>Referrer (previous website/page)</li>
                        <li>IP address (for unique visitor counting, not stored long-term)</li>
                        <li>Device type (parsed from User-Agent)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Your explicit consent under GDPR Article 6(1)(a).
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Security:</strong> HttpOnly (server-side only), Session cookie (deleted on browser
                        close).
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Retention:</strong> Analytics data retained for 24 months maximum for statistical
                        analysis.
                    </p>

                    <h4>sessionID_client (Session)</h4>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Purpose:</strong> Client-side duplicate of sessionID. Allows JavaScript to send page
                        duration data when you leave a page (using Navigator.sendBeacon API).
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Data Stored:</strong> Same UUID as sessionID.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Why Needed:</strong> HttpOnly cookies cannot be read by JavaScript. This cookie enables
                        accurate page duration tracking by sending data on page unload.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Your explicit consent under GDPR Article 6(1)(a).
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Security:</strong> NOT HttpOnly (readable by JavaScript), but contains no personal
                        information - only a random session identifier.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">2.4. What We DON'T Use</h3>
                    <p>
                        Axiom Hub's does <strong>NOT</strong> use:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>❌ Third-party advertising cookies</li>
                        <li>❌ Social media tracking cookies (Facebook Pixel, Twitter, etc.)</li>
                        <li>❌ Third-party analytics (Google Analytics, etc.)</li>
                        <li>❌ Behavioral tracking across websites</li>
                        <li>❌ Cookies for profiling or automated decision-making</li>
                        <li>❌ Roblox username storage in cookies (this was mentioned in old policy but is NOT
                            implemented)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        All cookies are first-party (set by axiomhub.eu domain only) and under our exclusive control.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Section 3: Legal Basis (GDPR) -->
                <h2 class="policy-section-title">3. Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR)</h2>
                <div class="policy-content">
                    <p>
                        Under GDPR Article 6, we process your personal data based on the following legal grounds:
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">3.1. Consent (Article 6(1)(a))</h3>
                    <p>
                        You provide explicit, informed, and freely given consent by clicking "Accept & Continue" on our
                        cookie banner. This consent covers:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Analytics cookies (sessionID, sessionID_client)</li>
                        <li>Collection of browsing behavior data</li>
                        <li>Page duration tracking</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        You can withdraw consent at any time by deleting cookies or contacting us.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">3.2. Contract Performance (Article 6(1)(b))</h3>
                    <p>
                        Authentication cookies (auth-token) are necessary to perform our contract with you - providing
                        access to authenticated areas and personalized services.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">3.3. Legal Obligation (Article 6(1)(c))</h3>
                    <p>
                        The consent cookie is required to comply with ePrivacy Directive and GDPR requirements to obtain
                        and record user consent.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">3.4. Legitimate Interest (Article 6(1)(f))</h3>
                    <p>
                        The "logged" cookie serves our legitimate interest in providing a functional user interface,
                        which does not override your fundamental rights and freedoms.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Section 4: Your GDPR Rights -->
                <h2 class="policy-section-title">4. Your Rights Under GDPR</h2>
                <div class="policy-content">
                    <p>
                        As a data subject, you have the following rights under the GDPR:
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">Right of Access (Article 15)</h3>
                    <p>
                        You can request a copy of all personal data we hold about you, including analytics data
                        associated with your session.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">Right to Rectification (Article 16)</h3>
                    <p>
                        You can request correction of inaccurate or incomplete personal data.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">Right to Erasure / "Right to be Forgotten" (Article 17)</h3>
                    <p>
                        You can request deletion of your personal data in the following circumstances:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Data no longer necessary for original purpose</li>
                        <li>You withdraw consent and no other legal basis exists</li>
                        <li>You object to processing and no overriding legitimate grounds exist</li>
                        <li>Data processed unlawfully</li>
                        <li>Legal obligation requires erasure</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">Right to Restriction of Processing (Article 18)</h3>
                    <p>
                        You can request temporary suspension of data processing while we verify accuracy or assess
                        legitimate grounds.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">Right to Data Portability (Article 20)</h3>
                    <p>
                        You can receive your personal data in a structured, machine-readable format (CSV, JSON) and
                        transmit it to another controller.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">Right to Object (Article 21)</h3>
                    <p>
                        You can object to processing based on legitimate interests or for direct marketing purposes.
                        We will cease processing unless we demonstrate compelling legitimate grounds.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">Right to Withdraw Consent (Article 7(3))</h3>
                    <p>
                        You can withdraw consent at any time by:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Deleting cookies from your browser settings</li>
                        <li>Contacting us at contact@axiomhub.eu</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        Withdrawal does not affect the lawfulness of processing before withdrawal.
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">Right to Lodge a Complaint (Article 77)</h3>
                    <p>
                        You have the right to lodge a complaint with your supervisory authority:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>France (CNIL):</strong> https://www.cnil.fr/</li>
                        <li><strong>UK (ICO):</strong> https://ico.org.uk/</li>
                        <li><strong>Germany (BfDI):</strong> https://www.bfdi.bund.de/</li>
                        <li>Find your country's authority: https://edpb.europa.eu/about-edpb/board/members_en</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="highlight-box">
                        <p>
                            <strong>How to Exercise Your Rights:</strong>
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Email: contact@axiomhub.eu</li>
                            <li>Discord: https://discord.gg/wx9gV9Z7Yy</li>
                            <li>Response time: Within 30 days (extendable to 60 days for complex requests)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Section 5: Data Retention -->
                <h2 class="policy-section-title">5. Data Retention Periods</h2>
                <div class="policy-content">
                    <p>
                        In accordance with GDPR Article 5(1)(e) (storage limitation principle), we retain your data only
                        as long as necessary:
                    </p>

                    <table class="policy-table">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Data Type</th>
                                <th>Retention Period</th>
                                <th>Reason</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Consent cookie</td>
                                <td>1 year</td>
                                <td>Legal requirement to maintain consent records</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Authentication cookies (auth-token, logged)</td>
                                <td>30 days or until logout</td>
                                <td>Session management and security</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Session cookies (sessionID, sessionID_client)</td>
                                <td>Until browser close</td>
                                <td>Session tracking during visit only</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Analytics database records</td>
                                <td>24 months maximum</td>
                                <td>Statistical analysis and service improvement</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>User account data</td>
                                <td>Until account deletion request</td>
                                <td>Providing ongoing service</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>

                    <p>
                        After expiration, cookies are automatically deleted from your browser. Database records are
                        automatically purged after 24 months or upon explicit deletion request.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Section 6: Data Security -->
                <h2 class="policy-section-title">6. Security Measures (Article 32 GDPR)</h2>
                <div class="policy-content">
                    <p>
                        We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to ensure a level of security
                        appropriate to the risk:
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">Technical Measures:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>HTTPS/TLS Encryption:</strong> All data transmission encrypted (TLS 1.2+)</li>
                        <li><strong>Secure Cookie Flags:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li><code>Secure</code>: Cookies only sent over HTTPS</li>
                                <li><code>HttpOnly</code>: Prevents JavaScript access (XSS protection)</li>
                                <li><code>SameSite=Strict/Lax</code>: CSRF attack prevention</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>JWT Token Security:</strong> Signed tokens with 30-day expiration</li>
                        <li><strong>Database Security:</strong> SQLite with Write-Ahead Logging (WAL), encrypted
                            connections</li>
                        <li><strong>Password Hashing:</strong> Argon2id (memory-hard, resistant to GPU attacks)</li>
                        <li><strong>Input Validation:</strong> Server-side validation and sanitization</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">Organizational Measures:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Access controls and authentication</li>
                        <li>Regular security audits</li>
                        <li>Data breach response procedures</li>
                        <li>Staff training on data protection</li>
                        <li>Privacy by design and by default</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">Data Breach Notification:</h3>
                    <p>
                        In the event of a personal data breach, we will:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Notify the supervisory authority within 72 hours (Article 33 GDPR)</li>
                        <li>Notify affected data subjects without undue delay if high risk (Article 34 GDPR)</li>
                        <li>Document all breaches in our breach register</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <!-- Section 7: International Transfers -->
                <h2 class="policy-section-title">7. International Data Transfers</h2>
                <div class="policy-content">
                    <p>
                        <strong>Cookie Storage:</strong> All cookies are stored locally on your device. No data is
                        automatically transferred to servers outside your control.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Server Location:</strong> Our servers are located within the European Union. We do not
                        transfer personal data to third countries outside the EEA without appropriate safeguards.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Third-Party Services:</strong> We do not use third-party services that transfer data
                        outside the EU. All processing is done on our own infrastructure.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        If we ever need to transfer data outside the EEA, we will use:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>EU Commission adequacy decisions (Article 45)</li>
                        <li>Standard Contractual Clauses (Article 46(2)(c))</li>
                        <li>Binding Corporate Rules (Article 47)</li>
                        <li>Explicit consent where appropriate</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <!-- Section 8: Analytics Details -->
                <h2 class="policy-section-title">8. Analytics and Tracking</h2>
                <div class="policy-content">
                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">8.1. What We Track</h3>
                    <p>
                        Our first-party analytics system collects the following data:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Page views:</strong> URLs visited, timestamps</li>
                        <li><strong>Session data:</strong> Unique session ID, duration</li>
                        <li><strong>User behavior:</strong> Page navigation, time on page</li>
                        <li><strong>Technical data:</strong> Browser type, device type (parsed from User-Agent)</li>
                        <li><strong>Referrer:</strong> Previous page/website (if provided by browser)</li>
                        <li><strong>IP address:</strong> Used for unique visitor counting, anonymized after 30 days</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">8.2. How We Use Analytics</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Understand how visitors use our website</li>
                        <li>Improve user experience and navigation</li>
                        <li>Identify popular content and features</li>
                        <li>Detect technical issues and errors</li>
                        <li>Plan infrastructure and capacity</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">8.3. IP Address Processing</h3>
                    <p>
                        IP addresses are personal data under GDPR. We process them as follows:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Count unique visitors, prevent analytics inflation</li>
                        <li><strong>Storage:</strong> Stored with analytics records for up to 24 months</li>
                        <li><strong>Anonymization:</strong> After 30 days, last octet removed (e.g., 192.168.1.xxx)</li>
                        <li><strong>No Sharing:</strong> Never shared with third parties</li>
                        <li><strong>No Profiling:</strong> Not used for automated decision-making or user profiling</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">8.4. Visit Deduplication</h3>
                    <p>
                        To prevent analytics inflation from page refreshes:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Same page visit within 30 seconds = counted once</li>
                        <li>Cached in memory (Map), cleared after 30 seconds</li>
                        <li>Improves data accuracy without tracking individual users</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">8.5. Page Duration Tracking</h3>
                    <p>
                        We measure how long you spend on each page using:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Method:</strong> JavaScript timer from page load to page unload</li>
                        <li><strong>Sending:</strong> Navigator.sendBeacon API (reliable even on page close)</li>
                        <li><strong>Events tracked:</strong> beforeunload, unload, visibilitychange (tab switch)</li>
                        <li><strong>Periodic updates:</strong> Every 30 seconds for long sessions</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <!-- Section 9: Children's Privacy -->
                <h2 class="policy-section-title">9. Children's Privacy (Article 8 GDPR)</h2>
                <div class="policy-content">
                    <p>
                        Our service is not directed at children under 16 years of age. We do not knowingly collect
                        personal data from children.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Roblox Integration:</strong> While Roblox is popular with younger users, our service
                        provides scripts and tools intended for users 16+. Authentication via Discord also requires
                        users to be 13+ (Discord ToS) or 16+ in the EU.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        If we discover we have collected personal data from a child under 16 without parental consent,
                        we will delete it immediately.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Parents:</strong> If you believe your child has provided personal data to us, please
                        contact us immediately at contact@axiomhub.eu.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Section 10: Third Parties -->
                <h2 class="policy-section-title">10. Third-Party Services and Data Sharing</h2>
                <div class="policy-content">
                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">10.1. Services We Use</h3>
                    <p>
                        We use the following third-party services (data processors under GDPR Article 28):
                    </p>

                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Discord OAuth:</strong> For optional authentication
                            <ul>
                                <li>Data shared: Discord user ID, email, username (with your consent)</li>
                                <li>Privacy policy: https://discord.com/privacy</li>
                                <li>Location: USA (Standard Contractual Clauses)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Email Service:</strong> For password reset emails
                            <ul>
                                <li>Provider: [Your SMTP provider]</li>
                                <li>Data shared: Email address, reset tokens (temporary)</li>
                                <li>Retention: Email logs deleted after 30 days</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">10.2. We DO NOT Share Data With:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>❌ Advertising networks</li>
                        <li>❌ Data brokers</li>
                        <li>❌ Social media platforms (except Discord OAuth with consent)</li>
                        <li>❌ Analytics companies</li>
                        <li>❌ Marketing companies</li>
                        <li>❌ Any other third party without explicit consent</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">10.3. Legal Disclosures</h3>
                    <p>
                        We may disclose personal data if required by law:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Court orders or legal process</li>
                        <li>Law enforcement requests (with valid legal basis)</li>
                        <li>Protection of our rights, property, or safety</li>
                        <li>Prevention of fraud or illegal activity</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        We will notify you of legal requests unless prohibited by law.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Section 11: Cookie Management -->
                <h2 class="policy-section-title">11. How to Manage and Delete Cookies</h2>
                <div class="policy-content">
                    <p>
                        You have full control over cookies. Here's how to manage them:
                    </p>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">11.1. Browser Settings</h3>

                    <h4>Google Chrome</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Settings → Privacy and security → Cookies and other site data → See all cookies and site
                            data</li>
                        <li>Search for "axiomhub.eu" and delete individual cookies</li>
                        <li>Or: Settings → Privacy → Clear browsing data → Cookies and site data</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4>Mozilla Firefox</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Settings → Privacy & Security → Cookies and Site Data → Manage Data</li>
                        <li>Search for "axiomhub.eu" and remove</li>
                        <li>Or: History → Clear Recent History → Cookies</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4>Microsoft Edge</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Settings → Cookies and site permissions → Manage and delete cookies and site data</li>
                        <li>Search for "axiomhub.eu"</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4>Safari (macOS)</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Preferences → Privacy → Manage Website Data</li>
                        <li>Search for "axiomhub.eu" and Remove</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4>Safari (iOS)</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Settings → Safari → Advanced → Website Data → Remove All Website Data</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="policy-subsection-title">11.2. Blocking Cookies</h3>
                    <p>
                        You can configure your browser to block all cookies or only third-party cookies. However:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>⚠️ Blocking all cookies will prevent you from using our service</li>
